comment: Deng (LAL) maintains legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Nelson (DEN) on the driving shot attempt.
Faried (DEN) makes incidental contact with Zubac (LAL) during rebounding.
Faried (DEN) maintains legal guarding position on Zubac (LAL) in the post and makes legal contact with the ball.
Russell (LAL) does not have part of his hand under the ball when he brings it to a pause and continues his dribble.
[Incidental or immaterial] Chandler (DEN) never fully cleanses the lane, keeping his foot on the lane line, and is not actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Zubac (LAL) sets the screen on Nelson (DEN) and firms up his position at the time of the contact.
Russell (LAL) makes marginal contact with Nelson (DEN) that does not affect his SQBR.
Zubac (LAL) makes contact with Faried's (DEN) body that affects his shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] PXP camera angle shows Russell (LAL) enters the area inside the three-point line prior to the free throw being released.
Harris (DEN) makes marginal contact with Russell (LAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Zubac (LAL) sets the screen on Harris (DEN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harris (DEN) makes contact with Zubac (LAL) that affects his SQBR.
Chandler (DEN) makes contact with Russell (LAL) that affects his SQBR.
Ingram (LAL) makes incidental contact with Chandler (DEN) that does not affect his SQBR.
Deng (LAL) legally contests the shot attempt by Chandler (DEN).
Faried (DEN) commits a take foul on Russell (LAL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that Faried (DEN) committed the off-ball foul following the release of the inbound.
